# Import the datetime module to get current time
import datetime 

# Print a greeting with hello 
print('Hello World!')

# Print current time
now = datetime.datetime.now()
print('Current date and time:')
print

The key points:

import datetime imports the datetime module to work with dates and times
print('Hello World!') prints the hello world string
now = datetime.datetime.now() gets the current datetime
now.strftime() formats the datetime in a readable string
print(now.strftime()) prints the formatted date and time















